[[=]]
+ [[span style="font-size: 150%;"]]LIVING IN UNDERVEGAS[[/span]]
[[/=]]

[[tabview]]

[[tab Twin Cities]]
++ LAS VEGAS
You know it. It's big, it's ugly, it's in the middle of the goddamn desert. Las Vegas is a monument to disgusting commercialism, human arrogance, the excess of capitalism, and the universal drive to be a total sucker and let someone take all your money. But Vegas isn't just the big casinos on the Strip -- Vegas is everywhere. Vegas is in a wedding chapel officiated by an Elvis impersonator. Vegas is in the guy dressed like an extremely copyrighted character who forces you into taking a photo then demands a fiver. Vegas is the //experience// -- of going out, blowing your money on blackjack, getting wasted in a bar, stumbling home but collapsing in an alley. And if you do all that in the right conditions on the right day, when the barriers between the cities aren't so firm, you might find yourself in...

++ UNDERVEGAS
Undervegas is the entertainment capital of Hell, but it's not a 1:1 copy of the upstairs neighbor. Look up and you don't see a light-polluted sky, but the stone roof of a gargantuan cavern. In many ways, it's the opposite: whereas Vegas is constantly tearing down old casinos to make room for the new, Undervegas is home to the ghostly remains of all the legendary Vegas casinos that met their untimely fate, from the Sands to the Magic Carpet. Where Vegas' party starts at night, the party in Undervegas never ends -- the city is one big festival, always partying on the streets, demons always finding something (or someone) to do. Undervegas is divided up into seven 'Estates', each primarily populated by one kind of demon and ruled by a Pit Boss, so the party can be very different depending on where you are in town. Whereas Vegas is an unwalkable nightmare you need a car to get around -- actually, maybe they're not totally different. 
[[/tab]]

[[tab Demonics]]
Per the Thorner System, Tartarean-class entities (demons) are grouped into seven distinct subtypes, each one correlating to a different deadly sin. Even within these subtypes, demon appearance and behavior can vary drastically.

||~ Class ||~ Details||
|| Arbor-class || Lust -- more commonly known as succubi or incubi, depending on which position they take. Suave, seductive, clingy.||
|| Avarice-class || Greed -- inconsistent appearance, consistent behaviors of constantly trying to increase their wealth. Rapacious, slippery, untrustworthy.||
|| Nimis-class || Gluttony -- generally huge forms from consuming everything they can. Lazy, large, excessive.||
|| Acedia-class|| Sloth -- Inadequately studied.||
|| Ira-class || Wrath -- confident, choleric, passionate, equate violence with both positive and negative emotions; always looking for a fight. Strong, stronger, strongest.||
|| Vainglory-class|| Envy --  Inadequately studied.||
||  Ego-class|| Pride -- extremely self-assured, powerful figures seeking to dominate others with their will. Confident, dominant, scheming.||


[[/tab]]

[[tab Site-666 & Co.]]
++ SITE-666
Publicly, Site-666 is the Luxor Las Vegas Hotel and Casino. The famous spotlights at the top are actually a complex piece of paratechnology that grounds the site and it's surroundings to baseline reality so they don't fall into Hell (again). Many of the hotel's suites are actually containment cells for high-value targets that the Foundation needs to keep happy; one of the upper rooms, blocked off from the rest of the Site, is the Director's Office. But the mass of the facility is underground, with 10 sublayers of dormitories, research labs, firing ranges, armories, containment cells, interrogation rooms, and everything else you can imagine. That's a lot of personnel. Here are the notable ones.

